## Foreign Keys

Foreign keys reference other tables.

### Naming Convention

```ruby
# Foreign key format: {model_name}_id
user_id       # References users.id
article_id    # References articles.id
category_id   # References categories.id
```

### Adding Foreign Keys

```ruby
# In migration
create_table :articles do |t|
  t.references :user, null: false, foreign_key: true
  # Creates user_id column with foreign key constraint
  
  t.string :title
  t.text :body
  
  t.timestamps
end

# Or add foreign key separately
add_reference :articles, :category, foreign_key: true

# With custom options
add_reference :articles, :user, 
              null: false,
              foreign_key: { on_delete: :cascade }
```

### Foreign Key Options

```ruby
# Cascade delete (delete dependent records)
foreign_key: { on_delete: :cascade }

# Nullify on delete (set to NULL)
foreign_key: { on_delete: :nullify }

# Restrict delete (prevent deletion if referenced)
foreign_key: { on_delete: :restrict }

# No action (database default)
foreign_key: true
```

